    <title>Oceans contributor: Alistair Hobday</title>
    <description>Alistair Hobday is a senior principal research scientist with CSIRO Oceans and Atmosphere in Hobart, Australia. His research covers spatial management and migration of large pelagic species, environmental influences on marine species, the impacts of climate change on marine resources and development and testing of adaptation options for marine conservation, fisheries and aquaculture.
</description>
